ParameterSection.Name: Control Mode

Parameter.Name: Motor Type or AFE

Parameter.Name: Control Strategy

ParameterSection.Name: Auto Restart
ParameterSection.Description: Used to restart the drive after a fault. Aimed at remote installations

Parameter.Name: AR Enable
Parameter.Description: Enables the Auto Restart function

Parameter.Name: AR Mode
Parameter.Description: Defines the mode of operation of the auto restart function. Trip reset only, standard auto restart or extended auto start.

Parameter.Name: AR Max Restarts
Parameter.Description: Defines the maximum number of automatic restart attempts before external intervention is required.

Parameter.Name: AR Trip Mask
Parameter.Description: Defines the trip events that can trigger the auto restart sequence.

Parameter.Name: AR Trip Mask 2
Parameter.Description: Defines the trip events that can trigger the auto restart sequence. Use in conjuncture with AR Trip Mask.

Parameter.Name: AR Initial Delay
Parameter.Description: Delay before the drive is restarted following the first time the drive is tripped

Parameter.Name: AR Repeat Delay
Parameter.Description: Delay before the drive is restarted following a repeated trip

Parameter.Name: AR Trip Mask B
Parameter.Description: Defines the trip events that can trigger the auto restart sequence.

Parameter.Name: AR Trip Mask 2 B
Parameter.Description: Defines the trip events that can trigger the auto restart sequence. Use in conjuncture with AR Trip Mask B and Delay B

Parameter.Name: AR Initial Delay B
Parameter.Description: Delay before the drive is restarted following the first time the drive is tripped. Associated with Mask B

Parameter.Name: AR Repeat Delay B
Parameter.Description: Delay before the drive is restarted following a repeated trip. Associated with Mask B

Parameter.Name: AR Active
Parameter.Description: Indicates that the auto restart module has a pending trip reset or drive restart.

Parameter.Name: AR Restart Pending
Parameter.Description: Indicates that the motor will restart once the trip sources are all clear and the delay timer has expired.

Parameter.Name: AR Restarts Remaining
Parameter.Description: Count of remaining restart attempts permitted until external intervention will be required.

Parameter.Name: AR Time Remaining
Parameter.Description: Time until drive restart will be attempted.

Parameter.Description: Sets the ramp up time to base speed when a change in speed is called for.

Parameter.Name: Duty Selection
Parameter.Description: When selected, selects Heavy Duty allowing higher continuous ratings with less overload capability ( typically 150%, 60s). Quadratic Torque operation is especially suited to fan or pump applications. When not selected, selects Normal Duty duty ( typically 110%, 60s). % are related to the Drive/stack ratings.

Parameter.Name: DC Link Voltage
Parameter.Description: This shows the voltage across the dc link capacitors.

Parameter.Name: Actual Speed RPM
Parameter.Description: This parameter changes according to the Control Mode: • In Sensorless Vec mode the parameter shows the calculated mechanical speed of the motor shaft in revolutions per minute. • In Closed Loop Vec mode the parameter shows the measured speed of motor shaft in revolutions per minute.• In Volts/Hz mode the parameter shows motor synchronous speed in rpm.

Parameter.Name: Actual Speed rps
Parameter.Description: This parameter changes according to the Control Mode: • In Sensorless Vec mode the parameter shows the calculated mechanical speed of the motor shaft in revolutions per second. • In Volts/Hz mode, the parameter shows the motor synchronous speed in revolutions per second.

Parameter.Name: Actual Speed Percent
Parameter.Description: This parameter changes according to the Control Mode: In Sensorless Vec mode the parameter shows the calculated mechanical speed of the motor shaft as a percentage of the user maximum speed setting (Max Speed in the Reference function). In Volts/Hz mode, the parameter shows the electrical drive output frequency as a percentage of the user maximum speed setting (Max Speed in the Reference function).

Parameter.Name: Fixed Boost
Parameter.Description: This parameter allows for no-load stator resistance voltage drop compensation. This correctly fluxes the motor (under no-load conditions) at low output frequencies, thereby increasing available motor torque. Fixed boost can be set in addition to auto boost and acceleration boost.

Parameter.Name: Auto Boost
Parameter.Description: This parameter allows for load dependent stator resistance voltage drop compensation. This correctly fluxes the motor (under load conditions) at low output frequencies, thereby increasing available motor torque. Auto Boost can be set in addition to Fixed Boost.

Parameter.Description: filter time constant

Parameter.Name: Search Mode
Parameter.Description: The type of speed search carried out by the flycatching sequence.

Parameter.Name: Search Volts
Parameter.Description: The percentage level of the search volts applied to the motor during the speed search phase of the flycatching sequence. Increasing this parameter improves the accuracy of the discovered motor speed but increases the braking influence of the speed search on the rotating motor.

Parameter.Name: Search Boost
Parameter.Description: The level of search boost applied to the motor during the speed search phase of the flycatching sequence.

Parameter.Name: Search Time
Parameter.Description: The search rate during the speed search phase of the flycatching sequence. Performing the flycatching speed search too quickly can cause the drive to inaccurately identify the motor speed. Refluxing at an inaccurate motor speed can cause the drive to trip on overvoltage. If this occurs, increasing this parameter will reduce the risk of tripping.

Parameter.Name: Min Search Speed
Parameter.Description: The lowest search speed before the speed search phase of the flycatching sequence is considered to have failed.

Parameter.Name: Flying Reflux Time
Parameter.Description: The rate of rise of volts from the search level to the working level after a successful speed search. Refluxing the motor too quickly can cause the Drive to trip on either overvoltage or overcurrent. In either case, increasing this parameter will reduce the risk of tripping.

Parameter.Name: flying load level
Parameter.Description: percentage of load level - V/Hz control

Parameter.Name: slew delta
